^-|cs||fp||va|4|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|This convention reverses (or "inverts") the strength of minor-suit raises. In "Standard," a raise from 1@C to 2@C (or 1@D to 2@D) shows 6-9 and a raise to 3-of-the-minor shows 10-12 (limit). |
PG| ***** 45 ***** |


AT|

If playing "Inverted," then the raise from 1@C to 2@C is 10-12 and the raise from 1@C to 3@C is weak (typically less than 7). There is a gap for hands of about 8-9 points (too strong for 3@C, but not strong enough for 2@C). When playing this convention, here are the discussion points:|
PG| ***** 46 ***** |


NT||
